## 7. Data fetching pattern (TanStack Query)

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { createQuery, createMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/svelte-query'

  const queryClient = useQueryClient()

  // Query
  const itemsQuery = createQuery(() => ({
    queryKey: ['list-items', listId],
    queryFn: async () => (await fetch(`/api/lists/${listId}/items`)).json(),
    staleTime: 0,
  }))

  // Mutation with invalidation
  const addMutation = createMutation(() => ({
    mutationFn: async (payload) => { ... },
    onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['list-items'] }),
  }))
</script>

{#if itemsQuery.data}...{/if}
```

Home page uses TanStack Query for list items so the grid updates immediately after adding media without a full page reload.

