## 11. UI conventions

### Select — always shadcn, never `<select>`

```svelte
import * as Select from '$lib/components/ui/select'

<Select.Root type="single" value={val} onValueChange={(v) => (val = v)}>
  <Select.Trigger class="h-9 text-sm">{label}</Select.Trigger>
  <Select.Content>
    <Select.Item value="opt" label="Option" />
  </Select.Content>
</Select.Root>
```

"All / none" sentinel: `'__all__'` (not empty string).

### Buttons

```svelte
<!-- outline -->
<button class="rounded-md border px-3 py-2 text-sm hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground">

<!-- primary -->
<button class="rounded-md bg-primary px-3 py-2 text-sm text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90">

<!-- destructive -->
<button class="rounded-md border border-destructive text-destructive hover:bg-destructive/10">
```

Global `transition-all duration-150`, `active:scale-[0.97]` applied via `app.css`.

### Dynamic colours — use `style=`, not dynamic Tailwind classes

```svelte
<!-- ✅ -->
<div style="background-color: {statusMeta.bgColor}">

<!-- ❌ Tailwind purge drops dynamic class names -->
<div class="bg-{color}">
```

### Scroll fade

```svelte
import { scrollFade } from '$shared/lib/scroll-fade'

<div class="scroll-fade overflow-y-auto" use:scrollFade>...</div>
```

Class `.scroll-fade` in `app.css` uses `mask-image` + CSS vars `--sf-top`/`--sf-bottom` to fade edges on scroll.

### Media card (reusable component)

`src/pages/home/ui/media-card.svelte` — used in **home** and **list-details**.

Props:

```typescript
type Props = {
  item: { status, currentSeason?, currentEpisode?, media: { id, title, year, posterUrl, overview, mediaType } }
  showStatusLabel?: boolean  // true in list-details, false (default) in home
}
```

### Countries

```svelte
import { formatCountry } from '$shared/lib/labels'
{formatCountry('US')}  // 🇺🇸 United States
```

### HTML from external APIs

```svelte
import { sanitizeHtml, stripHtml } from '$shared/lib/html'
{@html sanitizeHtml(media.overview)}  // detail page
{stripHtml(media.overview)}           // card preview
```

